    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains two-dimensional demographic data (age cohorts \u00d7 gender proportions) with 18 ordinal age categories and continuous percentage values. Synthetic data was generated maintaining original cohort totals while introducing realistic variance (\u03c3=0.15-0.3 across groups) and demographic patterns: 1) Bell-curve distribution peaking at 45-49 ages 2) Gender-specific longevity patterns visible in 80+ cohorts. The mirrored bar chart maximizes data-ink ratio by eliminating redundant axes while maintaining Tufte's principle of dual-axis comparison. Cairo's preattentive processing is leveraged through position (common percentage scale) and hue differentiation (blue=\u2642, red=\u2640). Statistical anchors: Male \u03bc=3.12% (\u03c3=1.28), Female \u03bc=3.24% (\u03c3=1.35), reflecting typical gender longevity differences."
